<title>USA: Computer Associates Q4 net, revs rise.</title>
<headline>Computer Associates Q4 net, revs rise.</headline>
<dateline>ISLANDIA, N.Y. 1997-05-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>COMPUTER ASSOCIATES INTERNATIONAL, INC.</p>
<p>(table in thousands, except per share data)</p>
<p>			     Three Months	    Fiscal Year</p>
<p>			   Ended March 31,	Ended March 31,</p>
<p>			     1997	 1996    1997 (A)   1996 (B)</p>
<p> Revenue	    $1,205,061 $1,110,422 $4,040,248 $3,504,629</p>
<p> Net Income	    336,008    265,099    963,941    751,680</p>
<p>Net Income per</p>
<p>    Common Share	   .90	  .70	 2.54	 1.99</p>
<p> Avg shrs		 374,998    380,036    379,183    378,371</p>
<p>NOTE: First Call Q4 consensus earnings estimate: $0.89 a share.</p>
<p>Results shown prior to writeoff of research and development costs.</p>
<p>(A)  Excludes the third quarter write-off of $598,000,000 for purchased research and development associated with the acquisition of Cheyenne Software, Inc.  With this write-off, income before taxes would be $932,301,000, net income would be $365,941,000, and net income per share would have been $.97 (see table below).  </p>
<p>(B)  Excludes the write-off of $1,303,280,000 (pre-tax) for purchased research and development associated with the acquisition of Legent Corporation.  With this write-off, loss before taxes would be $100,611, net loss would be $56,354 and net loss per share would have been $.16 (see table below).</p>
<p>All earnings per share and common share amounts have been adjusted to reflect the three-for-two stock splits effective June 19, 1996 and August 21, 1995.  </p>
